other net realized investment gains
other net realized investment gains in 2014 included $35million of net realized gains resulting from the sale of substantially
all of one of the company's real estate joint venture investments. the
table of contents
remaining
$70million of other net realized gains in 2014 were primarily driven by $32million of net realized investment gains related to fixed maturity investments, $24million
of net realized investment
gains related to equity securities, $8million of net realized investment gains related to other investments and $6million of net realized investment gains from real estate sales.
other
net realized gains in 2013 of $181million were primarily driven by $115million of net realized gains associated with u.s. treasury futures contracts, which require
daily mark-to-market settlement and are used from time to time to shorten the duration of the company's fixed maturity investment portfolio. the remaining $66million of other net realized
investment gains in 2013 were primarily driven by $41million of net realized investment gains related to fixed maturity investments, $15million of net realized investment gains related
