the
loss and loss adjustment expense ratio of 60.8% in 2013 was 3.5points lower than the loss and loss adjustment expense ratio of 64.3% in 2012. catastrophe losses in 2013 and
2012 accounted for 2.5points and 6.5points, respectively, of the loss and loss adjustment expense ratio. net favorable prior year reserve development in 2013 and 2012 provided
3.0points and 4.6points of benefit, respectively, to the loss and loss adjustment expense ratio. the 2013 underlying loss and loss adjustment expense ratio was 1.1points lower
than the 2012 ratio on the same basis, reflecting the impact of earned pricing that exceeded loss cost trends, partially offset by the impact of a change in business mix due to an increase in
longer-tail loss-sensitive business in national accounts.
